Reference-contexts: The relevant measures of error are the proximity of the shadow to the numerical solution, and the length of time before a glitch occurs. In gravitational N-body systems, glitches seem to occur most often at close encounters between particles <ref> (Quinlan & Tremaine, 1992) </ref>. Glitches do not necessarily imply no shadow exists, only that our algorithm failed to find one.
